{"id":"8259","name":"Good Morning, RSS!","tagline":"The First Personalised RSS Reader!","icon":"ios14 c4292093695 g61440","latest":"25071","description":"\n\t\t\t\t\t<h2> The Personalised RSS Reader that you’ve always wanted is here! </h2>\n\n<p><i>“Good Morning, RSS!”</i> is a shortcut that is designed to be run within a time-based automation, so that you can wake up and read articles from multiple of your favourite websites!  </p><ul>\n<br><br>\n<h5>Customisation:<br></h5>\nHere are a list of features that you can personalise to your liking:<br>\n<b>Adding any RSS Feed of your choice!</b><p>It goes without saying...<b><br>Choose how many RSS Articles you would like to read!</b><br>\nThis is useful for many reasons. Here are some examples:\n</p><ul>\n<li>Finding out about a new upload from your favourite YouTuber.*</li>\n<li>Checking for any changes to the status of a server you access on a regular basis.\n</li><li>There could even be other reasons!*</li>\n</ul><br>\n<b>Automatic reading timer!</b><br>\nWhen you go to customise the shortcut, you can input how many seconds per word you would like to be given. Say that you put 1 second per word, and your article is 120 words long... <br><b><i>You would get 2 minutes to read the article before it displays the next one!</i></b><i><br>\nComing soon: Reading speed calculator</i><br>\n<br>\n<h5>Other Features</h5>\n<ul><li>UpdateKit Integration<dd>This will allow me to fix bugs, adjust default values for convenience, or even make the import questions easier to understand. If you think I should make any changes as specified above, please let me know.</dd></li>\n<li>QuickUpdate Integration<dd>A lightweight version of UpdateKit that comes packaged within the shortcut, giving users the option to update without needing to install additional software.</dd></li>\n<li>Import Questions<dd>This is what makes all of the customisation options possible, and each question even has a clear explanation of how you should answer, so as to avoid any potential nuances...</dd></li>\n<li>Embedded RSS Articles<dd>By using never-before-seen** processing techniques, <i>”Good Morning, RSS!”</i> allows you to read articles from your favourite feed by simply expanding a notification.</dd></li></ul>\n<br>\n<br>\n<h5>Screenshots:</h5><br>\n<b>What the shortcut looks like during runtime:\n<img src=\"“https://www.dropbox.com/s/1repysda0yhit7u/403EA57E-480B-433D-AA37-1E4D2B2EC01A.png?dl=1”\"><br>\nRSS Articles Embedded within Notifications:\n<img src=\"“https://www.dropbox.com/s/lpxl7kinb9xwfh9/825F3C43-89C4-4F10-9F11-C0F74DB22090.png?dl=1”\">\nHow the RSS Reader calculates your reading time per article (with 0.35 being the customised reading speed):\n<img src=\"“https://www.dropbox.com/s/4ok1rbbmd074caf/2E135B67-1690-4C13-8EDF-960632CBC22B.jpeg?dl=1”\"><p></p>\n</b><p><b></b>*= May require specialist software and/or equipment.</p></ul>\n\t\t\t\t","releasenotes":"<p><strong>1.0.0.2 - Feb. 5, 2021, 7:59 p.m.</strong></p><p>Added “QuickUpdate: Integrated Edition”, allowing users to choose their preferred updater at the end of runtime.</p>"}